@(186 = 186-197) @wDN{Nanna-Suen} will cause six hundred ewes to give birth to lambs for the house of @wDN{Enlil}, for he will cause their rams to be let loose among them, and he will distribute them along the banks of the @wWN{Surungal} canal. @wDN{Ašimbabbar} will cause six hundred she-goats to give birth to kids for the house of @wDN{Enlil}, for he will cause their bucks to be let loose among them, and he will distribute them along the banks of the @wWN{Surungal} canal. @wDN{Nanna-Suen} will cause six hundred cows to give birth to calves for the house of @wDN{Enlil}, for he will cause their bulls to be let loose among them, and he will distribute them along the banks of the @wWN{Surungal} canal.

@(198 = 198-202) @wSN{Enegir} lay ahead of the offerings, @wSN{Urim} lay behind them. She brought out of the house what should not come out of the house, what should not come out of the house -- @wDN{Ningirida} brought out of the house what should not come out of the house: @q[Ningirida,Nanna-Suen]{“Welcome, welcome, welcome, O boat! O boat of @wDN{Suen}, welcome, welcome, O boat!”}

@(203 = 203-208) She laid out flour before the barge and spread bran. At her feet stood a covered bronze @fsux{gakkul} vat. 
{@noteanchor{1 ms. adds 1 line:} With her fingers she pulled out the boxwood bung (?) for him (declaring):
}  @q[Ningirida,Nanna-Suen]{“I shall rub precious oil on this peg. May ghee, syrup and wine be abundant in your midst, may the @fsux{suḫur} carp and the @fsux{eštub} carp rejoice at the prow of your boat!”} But the boat did not give her its cargo: @q[Nanna-Suen,Ningirida]{“I am going to @wSN{Nibru}!”}

@(209 = 209-213) @wSN{Larsam} lay ahead of the offerings, @wSN{Enegir} lay behind them. She brought out of the house what should not come out of the house, what should not come out of the house -- the lovely @wDN{Šerida} brought out of the house what should not come out of the house: @q[Cerida,Nanna-Suen]{“Welcome, welcome, welcome, O boat! O boat of my father, welcome, welcome, O boat!”}

