@(253 = 253-257) @wSN{Nibru} lay ahead of the offerings, @wSN{Tummal} lay behind them. At the Shining Quay, the quay of @wDN{Enlil}, @wDN{Nanna-Suen} finally docked the boat. At the White Quay, the quay of @wDN{Enlil}, @wDN{Ašimbabbar} finally docked the boat.

@(258 = 258-264) He stood at the grand stairway of his father who begot him and called out to the porter of his father who begot him: @q[Nanna-Suen,Kalkal]{“Open the house, porter, open the house! Open the house, @wDN{Kalkal}, open the house! @wDN{Kalkal}, doorkeeper, open the house! Doorman, doorkeeper, open the house! Porter, open the house! @wDN{Kalkal}, open the house!”}

@(265 = 265-274) @q{“I, @wDN{Nanna-Suen}, have gathered bulls for the cow-pen for the house of @wDN{Enlil}; porter, open the house. I, @wDN{Ašimbabbar}, have collected (?) fattened sheep for the house of @wDN{Enlil}; porter, open the house. I, @wDN{Nanna-Suen}, shall purify the cow-pen for the house of @wDN{Enlil}; porter, open the house. I, @wDN{Ašimbabbar}, shall feed meal to the goats for the house of @wDN{Enlil}; porter, open the house. I, @wDN{Nanna-Suen}, have …… porcupines for the house of @wDN{Enlil}; porter, open the house.”}

@(275 = 275-283) @q{“I, @wDN{Ašimbabbar} -- I, @wDN{Ašimbabbar} -- have …… long-tailed bush-rats for the house of @wDN{Enlil}; porter, open the house. I, @wDN{Nanna-Suen}, have gathered (?) turtles (?) and little birds for the house of @wDN{Enlil}; porter, open the house. I, @wDN{Ašimbabbar}, have brought small @fsux{ubi} birds from the pond for the house of @wDN{Enlil}; porter, open the house. I, @wDN{Nanna-Suen}, have brought small @fsux{azagun} birds from the pond for the house of @wDN{Enlil}; porter, open the house.”}

@(284 = 284-293) @q{“I, @wDN{Ašimbabbar}, …… @fsux{suḫur} carp for the house of @wDN{Enlil}; porter, open the house. I, @wDN{Nanna-Suen}, …… @fsux{eštub} carp for the house of @wDN{Enlil}; porter, open the house. I, @wDN{Ašimbabbar}, shall pour the oil of rushes onto the water for the house of @wDN{Enlil}; porter, open the house. I, @wDN{Nanna-Suen}, have filled baskets with eggs for the house of @wDN{Enlil}; porter, open the house. I, @wDN{Ašimbabbar}, have caused old reed and fresh reed to thrive for the house of @wDN{Enlil}; porter, open the house.”}

@(294 = 294-305) @q{“I, @wDN{Nanna-Suen}, have caused six hundred ewes to give birth to lambs for the house of @wDN{Enlil}, for I have caused their rams to be let loose among them, and I have distributed them along the banks of the @wWN{Surungal} canal; porter, open the house. I, @wDN{Ašimbabbar}, have caused six hundred she-goats to give birth to kids for the house of @wDN{Enlil}, for I have caused their bucks to be let loose among them, and I have distributed them along the banks of the @wWN{Surungal} canal; porter, open the house. I, @wDN{Nanna-Suen}, have caused six hundred cows to give birth to calves for the house of @wDN{Enlil}, for I have caused their bulls to be let loose among them, and I have distributed them along the banks of the @wWN{Surungal} canal; porter, open the house.”}

@(306 = 306-308) @q{“Porter, open the house! @wDN{Kalkal}, open the house! I will give you that which is in the prow of the boat as a first offering, and I will give you that which is in the stern of the boat as a last offering.”}


@(309 = 309-318) Rejoicing, the porter rejoicing, the porter rejoicing opened the house. @wDN{Kalkal}, the doorkeeper, rejoicing, the porter rejoicing opened the house. @wDN{Kalkal}, in charge of the bolt-handle, rejoicing, the porter rejoicing opened the house. At the house of @wDN{Enlil}, ……, @wDN{Nanna-Suen} made the offerings. @wDN{Enlil}, rejoicing over the offerings, offered bread to @wDN{Suen}, his son.

@(319 = 319-325) @wDN{Enlil} rejoiced over @wDN{Suen} and spoke kindly: @q[Enlil,Kalkal]{“Give sweet cakes to my little fellow who eats sweet cakes. Give sweet cakes to my @wDN{Nanna} who loves eating sweet cakes. Bring out from the @wTN{E-kur} the bread allotment and first quality bread for him. Pour out for him the finest beer, my pure ……. May the …… of the towering @fsux{tilimda} vessels, standing on the ground, ……. Order pure sweet cake, syrup, crescent (?) cake and clear water for him.”}

@(326 = 326-330) @wDN{Suen} replied to his father who begot him: @q[Nanna-Suen,Enlil]{“Father who begot me, I am indeed satisfied with what you have given me to eat. O Great Mountain, father who begot me, I am indeed satisfied with what you have given me to drink. Wherever you lift your eyes, there is kingship. O @wDN{Enlil}, your abundance is …….”}

@(331 = 331-339) @q{“Give to me, @wDN{Enlil}, give to me -- I want to set off for @wSN{Urim}! In the river give me the carp-flood -- I want to set off for @wSN{Urim}! In the fields give me speckled barley -- I want to set off for @wSN{Urim}! In the marshes give me @fsux{kuda} carp and @fsux{suḫur} carp -- I want to set off for @wSN{Urim}! In the reedbeds give me old reed and fresh reed -- I want to set off for @wSN{Urim}! In the forests give me the ibex and wild ram -- I want to set off for @wSN{Urim}! In the high plain give me the @fsux{mašgurum} tree -- I want to set off for @wSN{Urim}! In the orchards give me syrup and wine -- I want to set off for @wSN{Urim}! In the palace give me long life -- I want to set off for @wSN{Urim}!”}


@(340 = 340-348) He gave to him, @wDN{Enlil} gave to him -- and he set off for @wSN{Urim}. In the river he gave him the carp-flood -- and he set off for @wSN{Urim}. In the field he gave him speckled barley -- and he set off for @wSN{Urim}. In the pond he gave him @fsux{kuda} carp and @fsux{suḫur} carp -- and he set off for @wSN{Urim}. In the reedbeds he gave him old reed and fresh reed -- and he set off for @wSN{Urim}. In the forests he gave him the ibex and wild ram -- and he set off for @wSN{Urim}. In the high plain he gave him the @fsux{mašgurum} tree -- and he set off for @wSN{Urim}. In the orchards he gave him syrup and wine -- and he set off for @wSN{Urim}. In the palace he gave him long life -- and he set off for @wSN{Urim}.

@(349 = 349-352) My king, on your throne, for @wDN{Enlil}, may @wDN{Nanna-Suen} make you be born for seven days. On your holy throne, for the great mother @wDN{Ninlil}, may Lord @wDN{Ašimbabbar} make you be born for seven days.



